<task id="032" project="ai-document-summary">
  <metadata>
    <title>AI Authorization Filter</title>
    <phase>4: API Endpoints</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <blocks>none</blocks>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create or reuse authorization filter for AI endpoints that verifies user has read access
    to the sprk_document record before allowing summarization.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in ASP.NET Core authorization, Dataverse permissions, and endpoint filters.
    Follow ADR-008 for endpoint filter authorization pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    AI endpoints use authorization filter that checks Dataverse permissions.
    Unauthorized users receive 403 Forbidden.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Users should only be able to summarize documents they have access to.
      This prevents unauthorized information disclosure via the AI summary.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Filters/AiAuthorizationFilter.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Use endpoint filter pattern - no global middleware</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Check read access to sprk_document entity</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Reuse existing UAC infrastructure if available</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>docs/reference/adr/ADR-008-endpoint-filters-for-auth.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Filters/</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Authorization Filter" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Filters/">
        Follow existing DocumentAuthorizationFilter pattern
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Review existing authorization filters in Api/Filters/</step>
    <step order="2">Determine if existing filter can be reused or if new filter needed</step>
    <step order="3">If new: Create AiAuthorizationFilter implementing IEndpointFilter</step>
    <step order="4">Extract documentId from request body</step>
    <step order="5">Query Dataverse for user's access to sprk_document record</step>
    <step order="6">Return 403 Forbidden if not authorized</step>
    <step order="7">Apply filter to AI endpoints in SummarizeEndpoints.cs</step>
    <step order="8">Create unit tests for authorization scenarios</step>
    <step order="9">Run tests and verify all pass</step>
    <step order="10">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change this task's status to âœ… completed</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build and test .NET projects</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Filters/AiAuthorizationFilter.cs</output>
    <output type="test">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Filters/AiAuthorizationFilterTests.cs</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given user without document access, when calling AI endpoint, then returns 403.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given user with document access, when calling AI endpoint, then request proceeds.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given batch request, when user lacks access to any document, then returns 403.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All unit tests pass.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Consider caching permission checks for batch operations to reduce Dataverse queries.
    Existing DocumentAuthorizationFilter may be directly reusable.
  </notes>
</task>
